heir difficulty in expressing themselves coherently and comprehensively in one of the two agoras - Jewish or Christian – in which they were involved as literati and writers. The present edition and study of Abravanel’s Portuguese and Hebrew letters sheds a new light on the complexity of this new figure of the Jewish humanist.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Hebrew.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aJewish philosophersvCorrespondence. 0aJewish statesmenzItalyvCorrespondence. 0aJewish statesmenzPortugalvCorrespondence. 0aJewish statesmenzSpainvCorrespondence. 0aRabbisvCorrespondence. 4aHumanismus. 4aJuden /Geschichte. 4aRenaissance. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh  aHumanism.  aLetter writting.  aRenaissance Judaism.  aRenaissance Portuguese literature.1 aCohen Skalli, Cedric, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2007z9783110277135oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2007z9783110277050oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311019492040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089666440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110896664423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110896664/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2007  aZDB-23-DGGb2007  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014